Aego = Heroism+Shield of Words+Symbol of Marzin<br>
Blessing of Aegolism= Heroic bond+Sheild of words+Marzins Mark<br>
So, to answer your question, Bulwark of Faith doesn't stack with Aego (being the same line as Sheild of words)<br>
<br>
PoG+Bulwark+Marzins Mark is the highest hp/ac combo in the game, mana intense for the cleric though.<br>
<br>
When I'm MT for my guild, here are the buffs that I normally have up.<br>
<br>
Grim Aura (from earring)<br>
Regen<br>
Call of Earth<br>
Call of the Predator<br>
Brells Mountanous Barrier<br>
Focus of Spirit<br>
Riotous Health (or group version)<br>
Agility buff <br>
Aegolism<br>
Visions of Granduer<br>
Circle of Seasons<br>
Group Resist Magic<br>
Talisman of Eruptation.<br>
(space for a celestial elixor)<br>
<br>
That's 14 buff slots, leaving room for 2 more.. so I could easily replace Aego with PoG/MM/BoF, especially in places where resists aren't helpfull. However, once i get my grubby mitts on a primal weapon, something (/bye regen) has to go, or i'm going to want Aego and t'hell with the extra hps. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzebedi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zebedi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~zebedi/images/smallz.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/3/02 4:25:20 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#333399>- </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove>The Druids Grove</a><font color=#333399> - </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral>General - EQ</a> <font color=#333399> - </font><a href="http://www.thedruidsgrove.org">The Druids Grove</a><font color=#333399> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

